# Dark Mode Rules

This app uses `next-themes` with class strategy (`.dark` on `<html>`). Every visible color must have a `dark:` counterpart.

## Required pairings

| Light | Dark |
|-------|------|
| `bg-white` | `dark:bg-neutral-900` or `dark:bg-neutral-950` |
| `text-neutral-900` | `dark:text-neutral-100` |
| `text-neutral-600` | `dark:text-neutral-400` |
| `text-neutral-500` | `dark:text-neutral-400` |
| `border-neutral-200` | `dark:border-neutral-800` |
| `border-neutral-300` | `dark:border-neutral-700` |
| `text-red-600` | `dark:text-red-400` |
| `text-green-600` | `dark:text-green-400` |
| `hover:bg-neutral-50` | `dark:hover:bg-neutral-900` |

## Select and input elements

All `<select>` and `<input>` elements with custom className must include:
- `dark:bg-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100` (or use the `<Input>` component)
- `dark:border-neutral-700` or `dark:border-neutral-800`

## Never use

- Bare `text-neutral-500` without `dark:text-neutral-400`
- Bare `text-red-600` without `dark:text-red-400`
- `style={{ color: ... }}` or `style={{ background: ... }}` — use Tailwind classes
- Bare `bg-white` without a `dark:bg-*` counterpart

## Sidebar collapsed group icons

All top-level group header badges in the collapsed sidebar must use a consistent blue theme with dark mode support:

| Element | Light | Dark |
|---------|-------|------|
| Badge background | `bg-blue-100` | `dark:bg-blue-900` |
| Icon text color | `text-neutral-900` | `dark:text-white` |

Do NOT use different background colors (e.g. yellow, emerald, violet) for different groups. Keep them uniform blue.

All group header badges must use the `FloatingTooltip` component (not native `title` attribute) for consistent hover indicators across both top-level and admin-section menus.

No `<Separator>` dividers between collapsed group icons — spacing via `py-1` is sufficient.

## Shared components with built-in dark mode

Use these instead of raw HTML where possible:
- `<Input>` — already has full dark mode
- `<Card>` — already has full dark mode
- `<Badge>` — all variants have dark mode
- `<Button>` — all variants have dark mode
- `<Dialog>` — already has full dark mode
